cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.HC, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 

- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the social aspects of creativity and how systems mobilize large numbers of people to engage in creative tasks. This falls under the domain of computers and society. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper analyzes different types of systems (games, contests, and networks) with respect to the tasks performed and outputs generated. This falls under the domain of social and information networks. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper discusses how systems that generate collective creativity can be improved and how new systems might be constructed. This falls under the domain of software engineering. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the social aspects of creativity and how systems can be designed to facilitate collective creativity. This falls under the domain of human-computer interaction. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper discusses games as one of the types of systems that generate collective creativity. This falls under the domain of computer science and game theory.
